OL,6,FBenjamin Harrison pleaded guilty to
OL,7,Fknowingly permitting activity in
OL,8,Fcontravention of an environmental
OL,9,Fpermit and was jailed for eight months
OL,10,Fsuspended for 18 months. He was also
OL,11,Ftold to complete 150 hours unpaid work.
OL,13,FCouncillor Adrian Lythgoe, Lead Member
OL,14,Ffor Environment and Corporate Services
OL,15,Fsaid: "The actions of these men have
OL,16,Fnot only harmed our environment but
OL,17,Fhave also undermined the efforts of
OL,18,Fbusinesses that comply with the law,
OL,19,Fand they have cost the council and
OL,20,Fresidents unnecessary expense.
